[21]    L.P.Tongson, B. E. Knox, T.E. Sullivan, and S. J. Fonash, "Comparative study of chemical and polarization characteristics of Pd/Si and Pd/SiOx/Si Schottky-barrier-type devices," J. Appl. Phys., vol. 50, pp. 1535-1537, 1979.
[22]    C. T. Lu, K. W. Lin, H. I. Chen, H. M. Chuang, C. Y. Chen, and W.C. Liu, "A new Pd-Oxide-Al 0.3 Ga O.7As MOS hydrogen sensor," IEEE Electron Device Lett, vol.24，pp.390-392, 2003.
[23]    Y. Y. Tsai, K. W. Lin， C. T. Lu, H. I. Chen, H.M. Chuang， C. Y. Chen, C. C. Cheng， and W.C. Liu, "Investigation of hydrogen-sensing properties of Pd/AlGaAs-based Schottky diodes," IEEE Trans. Electron Devices, vol. 50, pp.2532- 2539, 2003.
[24]    C. C. Cheng， Y.Y. Tsai， K. W. Lin, H. I. Chen, W.H. Hsu, C.W. Hong, and W. C. Liu, "Temperature-dependent hydrogen sensing characteristics of a Pd/oxide/Al 0.24 Ga 0.76 As high electron mobility transistor，" IEEE electron. Lett., vol. 40, pp. 1608-1609， 2004.
[25]    C. C. Cheng, Y. Y. Tsai， K.W. Lin, H.I. Chen, W. H. Hsu, C.W. Hong, R. C. Liu， and W. C. Liu, "Pd-oxide-Al0.24Ga0.76As (MOS) high electron mobility transistor (HEMT)-based hydrogen sensor，" IEEE Sensors J., vol. 6, pp. 287-292， 2006.
[26]    L.G. Ekedahl， M. Eriksson and I. Lundstrom，“Hydrogen sensing mechanisms of metal-insulator interfaces，" Acc. Chem. Res.， vol. 31， pp.249-256, J998.
 
 
 
 





















